📝 AI / Figma Description

Design a Grades Page for ClassMate with the following specifications:

Navbar: Sticky, height 70px, dark/light mode based on accent color system. Title “Grades” using Playfair Display.
MP Tab Switch: Horizontal segmented tabs under the navbar for MP1 | MP2 | MP3 | MP4 | Semester. Selected tab uses primary/default; unselected uses bg/elevated. Sticky: no.
Classes List: Scrollable vertical list of class cards. Each card shows:

Class name

Teacher name

Grade (only visible on class detail page, not here)
Cards are rounded, shadowed, and fully clickable → navigate to specialized class page. No expanding cards.
Grade Circle (Class Detail Page): Big circle with fill color based on grade:

Purple: 97+

Blue: 93–97

Green: 88–93

Yellow: 80–88

Red: ≤80
White large text inside circle shows the grade.
Quick Actions: Sticky at bottom of scroll, single “Add Class” button. Full width, rounded.
Theme / Colors: Dark or light mode. Accent color system: user picks accent, app adjusts theme (backgrounds, text, buttons) to match accent.
Spacing & Layout: Page padding 16px, gap between cards 16px, scrollable main content.
Tokens / Colors: All backgrounds, text, shadows, borders, highlights use expanded token system.